  {
    "id": "85090131-d4c9-45d4-8f4f-f117c4b040d8",
    "sentence": "In our Summary of Economic Projections (SEP), Committee participants revised up their assessments of GDP growth this year but expect growth to cool, with the median projection falling to 1.4 percent next year.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20231213.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20231213",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9c018310-3623-4fbd-b330-c873b5c8385a",
    "sentence": "Economic activity expanded at a 6.5 percent pace in the first half of the year, reflecting progress on vaccinations, the reopening of the economy, and strong policy support.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20211103.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20211103",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "68065e00-3bec-41de-8e36-ca7a998e79ea",
    "sentence": "The median projection for the unemployment rate in the SEP is 4.2 percent at the end of this year and 4.3 percent over the next few years.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20241218.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20241218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "03ed2b3f-ffbf-4705-9a3f-b0b909d6d58d",
    "sentence": "The fact that unemployment measures have been holding steady while the number of jobs has grown solidly shows that more people, presumably in response to better employment opportunities and higher wages, have started actively seeking and finding jobs. This is a very welcome development, both for the individuals involved and the nation as a whole.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160921.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160921",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "af1e7ec0-50a4-48fc-9cb1-78ece85662e8",
    "sentence": "The pace of job growth has been strong recently, with job gains averaging nearly 280,000 per month over the past 3 months; over the past 12 months, job gains averaged nearly 230,000 per month.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20141217.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20141217",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d719de1c-522e-4423-a385-8d0abe854388",
    "sentence": "As we have said, we will provide advance notice before announcing any decision to make changes to our purchases.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210616.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210616",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b70ae252-b065-42cc-b8e4-7736f46f86ba",
    "sentence": "Returning to monetary policy, although the Committee decided at this meeting to maintain its target for the federal funds rate, we continue to expect that the ongoing strength of the economy will warrant gradual increases in that rate to sustain a healthy labor market and stabilize inflation around our 2 percent longer-run objective. That expectation is based on our view that the federal funds rate remains somewhat below its neutral level -- that is, the level that is neither expansionary nor contractionary and keeps the economy operating on an even keel.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170920.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170920",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d743c141-50ec-4c6f-9346-94618d01a21d",
    "sentence": "I would like to emphasize that the forecasts of the appropriate path of the federal funds rate are conditional on participants' individual projections of the most likely outcomes for economic growth, employment, inflation, and other factors. But our actual policy decisions over time will depend on evolving economic conditions.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20150617.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20150617",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fd035c9d-edd8-438a-b92e-4132616975b3",
    "sentence": "The median of participants' projections for the unemployment rate remains below 4 percent over the next several years.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20191211.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20191211",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d67d8b70-461e-4751-bb7f-c7023996e162",
    "sentence": "The median participant projects that the appropriate level of the federal funds rate will be 3.9 percent at the end of this year and 3.4 percent at the end of next year, unchanged from December.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250319.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250319",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aa8da087-116b-4761-9497-8dbaf77da377",
    "sentence": "The Committee also remains concerned that restrictive fiscal policies may slow economic growth and job creation in coming months.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20130320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c177a51b-0c72-4d45-a228-2005402ee1cf",
    "sentence": "Although real GDP declined in the first quarter, this decline appears to have resulted mainly from transitory factors.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140618.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140618",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1c10301b-3cee-48a3-ac42-6b4b4eef2ff3",
    "sentence": "The data since our January meeting have been generally consistent with our expectation that the fourth-quarter pause in the recovery would prove temporary and that moderate economic growth would resume.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20130320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f77c2787-b116-4185-9d6a-2fb3beb0f2dd",
    "sentence": "At today's meeting, the Committee raised the target range for the federal funds rate by 25 basis points, bringing the target range to 4½ to 4¾ percent. And we are continuing the process of significantly reducing the size of our balance sheet.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230201.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20230201",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "399c98c4-08ed-4d5a-9019-e685bfc5b855",
    "sentence": "To conclude: The Fed has been assigned two goals for monetary policy: maximum employment and stable prices.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20251210.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20251210",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d1df4a1a-b7e0-42e0-ac80-4656c853271c",
    "sentence": "However, if these headwinds abate, as we expect, the neutral federal funds rate should gradually move higher as well. This view is implicitly reflected in participants' projections of appropriate monetary policy.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160316.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160316",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "03b0d3b9-8156-4fc7-b202-3cbd2f28faac",
    "sentence": "And, while most of the incoming domestic economic data have been solid, some surveys of business and consumer sentiment have moved lower, giving reason for caution.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190130.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190130",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "11b2b220-e3c3-4eaa-83a2-ab4cfd6b08ca",
    "sentence": "The projections about the appropriate path of policy assume that the economy evolves broadly in line with the projections for growth, employment, unemployment, and inflation.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20180926.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20180926",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "017f5394-6c50-4d65-a70a-8c3c59230c3d",
    "sentence": "As we act to meet that obligation, we'll balance our maximum-employment and price-stability mandates, keeping in mind that, without price stability, we cannot achieve the long periods of strong labor market conditions that benefit all Americans.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250507.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250507",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0d4c9b8e-196a-43fa-b325-8d4df3ffdad0",
    "sentence": "Looking ahead, the Committee anticipates that the unemployment rate will decline gradually over the next several years, reflecting the moderate pace of economic growth.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20120425.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20120425",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0389def2-74c3-42b8-9c49-396643e8d7c6",
    "sentence": "The Committee's baseline expectations for economic activity, the labor market, and inflation have not changed much since December: With appropriate monetary policy, we continue to expect moderate economic growth, further labor market improvement, and a return of inflation to our 2 percent objective in two to three years.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160316.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160316",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b3231fd0-b9fc-439d-81dc-049140ab3af6",
    "sentence": "Market-based measures of inflation compensation have moved up considerably but are still low.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20161214.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20161214",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "21dad9ef-4efa-429a-b6cd-f5e222f58d03",
    "sentence": "In addition, the median estimate of the longer-run normal unemployment rate moved down a tenth to 4.6 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170614.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170614",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8a2f1f1f-6303-4458-ad90-fdbbdd97b20a",
    "sentence": "The median projection projects -- participant -- median participant projects that the appropriate level of the federal funds rate will be 3.9 percent at the end of this year, the same as projected in March.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250618.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250618",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "231bcc9e-7a66-4ed6-8d62-ced44954c60e",
    "sentence": "In coming months, we will receive a good amount of data that will help inform our assessment of the balance of risks and the appropriate setting of the federal funds rate.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250730.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250730",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "06bbf4ce-8e4d-420d-ba0f-216ba0525184",
    "sentence": "Finally, we made a small technical adjustment in one of our tools for implementing monetary policy: the interest rate on excess reserves, or IOER rate.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190501.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190501",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aecf5a53-641b-4208-b54a-faedbe143151",
    "sentence": "Employment in this sector and the economy as a whole remains well below pre- pandemic levels.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210616.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210616",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "844fca76-a3f8-44f3-882a-c737f4a8adb4",
    "sentence": "Although the median federal funds rate edged up this year and next, most participants did not revise their projections.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20180613.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20180613",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "650b2bcb-2959-4bc5-9205-1eb827cea0e4",
    "sentence": "Most participants see inflation gradually increasing toward the Committee's longer-run target; the central tendency of their projections for inflation is 1.3 to 1.7 percent this year and 1.7 to 2.0 percent in 2015.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20130320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7967c32d-84ab-4e24-81d0-1964e4d2ce92",
    "sentence": "Furthermore, survey measures and market indicators imply that longer-term inflation expectations have remained stable. Consequently, the Committee anticipates that, over coming quarters, inflation will settle at or below its mandate-consistent rate of 2 percent or a bit less.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20111102.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20111102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4bd5e670-2b46-4019-8869-89873b20568d",
    "sentence": "The unemployment rate is notably higher than it was a year ago but has edged down over the past three months and remains low at 4.1 percent in October.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20241107.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20241107",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ef2ec13e-6e6a-49bc-975a-408b816df50d",
    "sentence": "It is important, however, that monetary policy not overreact to any individual data point or short- term swing in sentiment.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190619.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190619",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "0912bb9c-c9d4-4150-970c-fec462fd8138",
    "sentence": "All of these policies are still evolving, however, and their effects on the economy remain highly uncertain.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250507.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250507",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "acbc6690-f13d-4fe5-8cbc-8359933d9b47",
    "sentence": "Overall, we continue to expect that the economy will expand at a moderate pace over the next few years.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170614.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170614",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "66eb0a09-38d8-4424-a60c-3ddc71abe789",
    "sentence": "For the past year, the Committee has said that the current low target range for the federal funds rate would be appropriate at least as long as the unemployment rate remained above 6½ percent, inflation was projected to be no more than half a percentage point above our 2 percent longer-run goal, and longer-term inflation expectations remained well anchored.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20131218.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20131218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f987db87-19af-473f-aee1-8dad821268d2",
    "sentence": "If the economy proves to be stronger than anticipated by the Committee, resulting in a more rapid convergence of employment and inflation to the FOMC's objectives, then increases in the federal funds rate target are likely to occur sooner and to be more rapid than currently envisaged.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140618.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140618",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4f781c18-089a-4c8b-b1e0-7c64664c871e",
    "sentence": "Broadly speaking, however, the spending and production data, while somewhat weaker than we had expected in January, are roughly in line with our expectations as of December, the last time Committee participants submitted economic projections.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140319.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140319",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8d7ba817-d79d-4c53-bb18-d64d91e5f8bb",
    "sentence": "Finally, in conjunction with our policy statement, we also released an implementation note that provides details on the tools that we are using to raise the federal funds rate into the new target range.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20151216.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20151216",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d1d3072b-8808-4f23-9603-f29d8b05bcc8",
    "sentence": "Nominal wage growth has been easing, and job vacancies have declined.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20240320.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20240320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4973614d-8df3-43a8-a366-6de56d114b0b",
    "sentence": "The Committee will continue its policy of reinvesting proceeds from maturing Treasury securities and principal payments from agency debt and mortgage-backed securities.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20151216.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20151216",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8712f921-df8b-4048-90c5-a68dc5367b60",
    "sentence": "Price stability is the responsibility of the Federal Reserve.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230503.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20230503",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "60b85c74-2309-4b73-b723-88f97056a7e4",
    "sentence": "Over coming months, we will be looking for compelling evidence that inflation is moving down consistent with inflation returning to 2 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220921.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220921",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "efffcb73-6eb6-4ab9-b781-6e26abed019f",
    "sentence": "The unemployment rate remained elevated at 6.7 percent in December, and participation in the labor market is notably below pre-pandemic levels.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210127.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210127",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "17a2efff-cea1-46ea-9397-41a6749f677e",
    "sentence": "Coming out of our last meeting in May, there was a broad sense on the Committee that a ½ percentage point increase in the target range should be considered at this meeting if economic and financial conditions evolved in line with expectations.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220615.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7cf9d9f9-eda2-46c7-8b6c-0dc1e8b5a6fb",
    "sentence": "Finally, the median inflation projection is 1.9 percent this year, 2 percent next year, and 2.1 percent in 2020.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20180321.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20180321",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "366e08fd-e3ba-419d-81dc-3d888c5f7f84",
    "sentence": "Although the recent surge in commodity prices has led inflation to pick up somewhat in the near term, the Committee continues to project inflation to return to mandate-consistent levels in the medium term, as I have discussed. Consequently, the short-term increase in inflation has not prompted the Committee to tighten policy at this juncture.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "cc82d887-5b0d-41da-a033-bcfb500c6e8c",
    "sentence": "Doing so would risk adding even more uncertainty to the outlook. Thus, my colleagues and I will be looking to see whether these uncertainties will continue to weigh on the outlook, and we will use our tools as appropriate to sustain the expansion.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190619.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190619",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b247dece-6960-436c-872e-21aece408db3",
    "sentence": "That's based on our view that the neutral nominal federal funds rate -- that is, the interest rate that is neither expansionary nor contractionary and keeps the economy operating on an even keel -- is currently quite low by historical standards. That means that the federal funds rate does not have to rise by all that much to get to a neutral policy stance.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170315.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bac48886-3076-40e5-85cf-f2736ec78f62",
    "sentence": "Our decisions will depend on the totality of incoming data and their implications for the outlook for economic activity and inflation. And we will continue to make our decisions meeting by meeting and communicate our thinking as clearly as possible.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20221214.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20221214",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "136f21de-bb6b-47d4-9c17-253c85892aa7",
    "sentence": "To address possible pressures in money markets over the year-end, we've been conducting term repo operations spanning year-end.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20191211.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20191211",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d5446c8d-326c-4d03-814b-b82bb701154a",
    "sentence": "Thank you, I will be happy to take your questions.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160615.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "06eea348-9cb5-4a64-baf0-ce0fabf2489d",
    "sentence": "Of course, inflation has been running somewhat below our goal of 2 percent, but we project that gap to close gradually over time.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20141217.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20141217",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "20398fb9-fdc6-4d34-9122-73b4f7defdf6",
    "sentence": "The overall recovery in economic activity since last spring is due in part to federal stimulus payments and expanded unemployment benefits, which have provided essential support to many families and individuals.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210127.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210127",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "28019eb6-32fa-4c4e-8b34-6a91988a1688",
    "sentence": "As I have often stressed, however, monetary policy has its limits; only the private and public sectors working together can get the U.S. economy fully back on track.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20121212.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20121212",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b217cf60-0272-4f9e-9ca3-990046ad6926",
    "sentence": "As you can see from the chart labeled \"Appropriate Timing of Policy Firming,\" Committee participants have a range of views about when the initial increase in the federal funds rate is likely to be appropriate. Following a careful discussion of those views at today's meeting, the FOMC maintained its collective judgment that economic conditions will likely warrant exceptionally low levels for the federal funds rate at least through late 2014.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20120425.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20120425",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dc46ef83-d479-4768-8582-05cc4e5a9094",
    "sentence": "Consumer spending has been robust over the past several quarters, even as high interest rates have weighed on housing and equipment investment.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20240501.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20240501",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "855164be-88d5-46ec-8fc0-dc71d59066dc",
    "sentence": "Over the 12 months through July, total PCE inflation was 1.4 percent and core inflation, which excludes volatile food and energy prices, was 1.6 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190918.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1e527c77-d34a-43ea-9666-caf4b01bff38",
    "sentence": "This underscores, for us, the importance of sustaining the expansion so that the strong job market reaches more of those left behind.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190918.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "89cc1cee-f526-4933-90d0-9317901ed9fb",
    "sentence": "Global supply chains are complex; they will return to normal function, but the timing of that is highly uncertain. We are committed to our longer-run goal of 2 percent inflation and to having longer-term inflation expectations well anchored at this goal.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20211103.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20211103",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4ad8d42f-3496-4dd4-9435-104d99ea9c49",
    "sentence": "It should be noted that these estimates are inherently uncertain and subject to revision, because longer-run rates of economic growth and unemployment are determined largely by nonmonetary factors that may evolve over time and that often cannot be directly measured.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110622.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110622",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a2b6eab9-231c-4428-a4b5-866318e0f599",
    "sentence": "Although some American families and communities continue to struggle and some longer-term economic problems remain, the strong economy is benefiting many Americans.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20181219.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20181219",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "556bd78e-5c2e-426d-b560-c08f2a7f7ae5",
    "sentence": "From there, Committee participants generally see the unemployment rate declining to its longer-run normal level by the end of 2016.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140618.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140618",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "cacbb843-718c-4ee9-ac50-a5499b3d2d7c",
    "sentence": "Although activity in the housing sector has picked up somewhat, it remains well below levels of a year ago, largely reflecting higher mortgage rates. And higher interest rates and slower output growth also appear to be weighing on business fixed investment.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230726.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20230726",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e93f1d49-cac4-4b03-b536-e08dcf2e6f74",
    "sentence": "We know that the best thing we can do to support a strong labor market is to promote a long expansion -- and that is only possible in an environment of price stability.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220316.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220316",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d63a31af-10b7-4e17-a5bf-970a83c9d3d3",
    "sentence": "Barring a very significant and unexpected weakening in the outlook, we do not intend to alter this program.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20180321.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20180321",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2745f027-da0d-4cac-b67b-416b39238592",
    "sentence": "The median projection for the appropriate level of the federal funds rate is 1.9 percent at the end of this year -- a full percentage point higher than projected in December.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220316.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220316",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bf1db0f1-aad0-44cb-bf99-969734c49a52",
    "sentence": "If this is so, we may hold the size of our asset holdings roughly constant for a time.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "9a4d3aa3-ab5d-4535-9dcf-65287cd96572",
    "sentence": "While the economy appears to be advancing at a moderate pace, with some improvements appearing in housing and elsewhere, FOMC participants see an economic outlook that remains uncertain.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20120913.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20120913",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "15e5dc43-c7db-4649-be52-77d9df7179eb",
    "sentence": "With today's action, we have raised interest rates by 3¾ percentage points this year.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20221102.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20221102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5b13aef4-118a-465a-a522-4c1aba128d25",
    "sentence": "Apart from temporary variations in energy prices, inflation is running somewhat below the Committee's longer-run objective of 2 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20130320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c6b3a833-426b-435e-bdec-5b2b4141eece",
    "sentence": "Business investment in equipment and intangibles has continued to expand, while activity in the housing sector remains weak.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20251029.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20251029",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8db24aad-2406-4cc6-8d4f-ef7abdd67e72",
    "sentence": "Once we begin to remove policy accommodation, we continue to expect that -- as we say in our statement -- \"even after employment and inflation are near mandate-consistent levels, economic conditions may, for some time, warrant keeping the target federal funds rate below levels the Committee views as normal in the longer run.\"",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20150617.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20150617",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "8f34dbcd-c090-4587-a674-1fb5da01d49c",
    "sentence": "If the economy remains strong and inflation does not continue to move sustainably toward 2 percent, we can maintain policy restraint for longer.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250319.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250319",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "060a599c-8b5a-402b-9fe8-da0cd1a8d829",
    "sentence": "GDP growth in the fourth quarter of last year came in at 3.2 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20240320.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20240320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "040dd2d2-268c-46a1-85eb-e0ca33ff2c23",
    "sentence": "We will need to be nimble in responding to incoming data and the evolving outlook. And we will strive to avoid adding uncertainty to what is already an extraordinarily challenging and uncertain moment.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220316.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220316",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bbae8e16-5099-4f26-a9e3-8cbed7cc17a1",
    "sentence": "Further, FOMC participants now see the risks around their forecasts of growth and unemployment as having become more nearly balanced, rather than tilted in an unfavorable direction as they were at the inception of the asset purchase program.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20131218.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20131218",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "373270cd-a789-48ef-ad30-8db0bbcf71ea",
    "sentence": "Participants generally revised up their growth projections since December, reflecting the strength of incoming data, including data on labor supply.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20240320.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20240320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "80f8367f-33f7-48a7-a80d-bd5896fe8055",
    "sentence": "The Committee will also consider whether the improvement in the unemployment rate appears sustainable.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20121212.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20121212",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3e5ca9ac-8fd0-4b89-a1ea-87d1878a87bc",
    "sentence": "Over the past three months, payroll job gains averaged 265,000 jobs per month.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20240320.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20240320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3017ae23-9af3-4fee-85a2-1bf259e8ee37",
    "sentence": "At today's meeting, the Committee raised the target range for the federal funds rate by 75 basis points. And we are continuing the process of significantly reducing the size of our balance sheet, which plays an important role in firming the stance of monetary policy.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20221102.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20221102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aac1bbb3-cd58-4f73-b32d-13d8beb1a671",
    "sentence": "Nonetheless, the labor market has a ways to go.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210728.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210728",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c9619ed6-d5a3-483f-99a1-553c5f55beff",
    "sentence": "Even after this increase, monetary policy remains accommodative, thus supporting some further strengthening in the job market and a sustained return to 2 percent inflation.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170315.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170315",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "42a28b3d-152d-4867-ba51-405296c6e294",
    "sentence": "There is significant uncertainty around that level of interest rates.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20221102.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20221102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b4e5538c-3026-4b42-a891-5b46121d5c31",
    "sentence": "At this meeting, the Committee continued its discussions as part of our five-year review of our monetary policy framework.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250730.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250730",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "97c3b5ae-7d88-4d50-b8cb-68ed1c21c0d6",
    "sentence": "In that regard, we will be prepared to adjust any of the details of our approach to balance sheet management in light of economic and financial developments.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220126.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220126",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "84beea8c-90b5-4f4e-a4b3-58ea22f4903f",
    "sentence": "The inflation data received earlier this year were higher than expected, though more recent monthly readings have eased somewhat.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20240612.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20240612",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fa0feb0e-5777-4fe4-b611-ef525053ef8f",
    "sentence": "Based on the consumer price index, or CPI, and other data, we estimate that total PCE prices rose 3.4 percent over the 12 months ending in August and that, excluding the volatile food and energy categories, core PCE prices rose 3.9 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230920.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20230920",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aecc83cd-0bfe-49a0-8863-7c23f71cd3b4",
    "sentence": "We will continue to make our decisions meeting by meeting and communicate our thinking as clearly as possible.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20221102.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20221102",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "91b5a176-ba5e-4519-847b-beaa71fb79db",
    "sentence": "Overall, our policy discussions focused on the appropriate response to the uncertain environment.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190619.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190619",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c0200894-d510-4a21-9b61-f2a64e7509b7",
    "sentence": "Also, it is important to note that the Committee makes its decisions on a meeting-by- meeting basis and does not and need not decide on a likely future path for the federal funds rate.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160316.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160316",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c91fb119-acbf-4b05-b307-10a229bd50f5",
    "sentence": "At our meeting that wrapped up today, the Committee made good progress on a plan for reducing our securities holdings, and we expect to announce the beginning of balance sheet reduction at a coming meeting.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220316.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220316",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "84a11d5a-8cd4-4c6a-87a2-1a8bcf55d8ce",
    "sentence": "The appreciation of the dollar has also weighed on inflation by holding down import prices.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20151216.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20151216",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aa6cffe7-a3d5-4fc1-95d1-0ce0ca5dc46b",
    "sentence": "Of course, it is far too early to know how these policies will unfold.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20161214.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20161214",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3f157177-73e2-4840-9f15-0d576afce960",
    "sentence": "Over the next few months, 12-month measures of inflation will move up as the very low readings from March and April of last year fall out of the calculation.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210317.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210317",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "4372d5df-3ce3-40d3-a211-fec1f395f383",
    "sentence": "This program, which was described in the June addendum to our Policy Normalization Principles and Plans, will gradually decrease our reinvestments of proceeds from maturing Treasury securities and principal payments from agency securities. As a result, our balance sheet will decline gradually and predictably.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170920.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170920",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bf52b4fa-eac4-48b7-8aaf-e9802ca88603",
    "sentence": "The Committee reiterated that it anticipates that ongoing increases in the target range will be appropriate. And we are continuing the process of significantly reducing the size of our balance sheet -- which plays an important role in firming the stance of monetary policy.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20220615.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20220615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "261201e8-c358-44dd-8ab4-fa5e5bb8140a",
    "sentence": "Business investment, which was weak for much of last year, has continued to expand. And exports have shown greater strength this year, in part reflecting a pickup in global growth.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20170614.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20170614",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "23eeb817-b150-4628-920a-df3a0473cee6",
    "sentence": "It's also possible that the inflationary effects could instead be more persistent. Avoiding that outcome will depend on the size of the tariff effects, on how long it takes for them to pass through fully into prices, and, ultimately, on keeping longer-term inflation expectations well anchored.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250618.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20250618",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e8ff362b-6d1f-4739-a053-a4d52ead44ca",
    "sentence": "Economic growth was relatively weak late last year and early this year.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160615.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6cd7ee35-66db-4cb5-88ea-7e108c1179ae",
    "sentence": "In contrast, labor market conditions have continued to improve.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140319.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140319",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3e9febf3-49e7-4219-896a-6f80acf8392f",
    "sentence": "In the near term, risks to inflation are tilted to the upside and risks to employment to the downside -- a challenging situation.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20251210.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20251210",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a1d1fd27-e14e-4d81-83a5-0b81d0e22498",
    "sentence": "Finally, the Committee will continue its policy of reinvesting proceeds from maturing Treasury securities and principal payments from agency debt and mortgage-backed securities.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20160615.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20160615",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d7a26cfb-1c3c-4bb4-a469-0b2370232f12",
    "sentence": "With inflation currently still low, why is the Committee raising the federal funds rate target?",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20151216.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20151216",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "518ad70d-9221-42fd-89a5-d9e0cd6afd80",
    "sentence": "The median Committee participant's assessments of the neutral rate of interest and the longer-run normal rate of unemployment have also declined this year, reinforcing the case for a somewhat lower path for our policy rate. These changes in the anticipated path of interest rates have eased financial conditions and have supported the economy.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190731.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190731",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "696c027b-f669-47e4-b8d9-294ac2a375e4",
    "sentence": "As I have noted frequently, the economic conditions we have set out as preceding any future rate increase are thresholds, not triggers. For example, a decline in the unemployment rate to 6½ percent would not lead automatically to an increase in the federal funds rate target, but would, instead, indicate only that it had become appropriate for the Committee to consider whether the broader economic outlook justified such an increase.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130918.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20130918",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "719e3902-afd9-4e12-9a88-4764c7521894",
    "sentence": "Monthly job gains in May were lower than expected, however, and, in light of recent developments, this bears watching.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190619.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190619",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "dd799208-da51-4870-95e3-816a008f9a31",
    "sentence": "Reducing inflation is likely to require a period of below-trend growth and some softening in labor market conditions.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230322.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20230322",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "bbe4bfee-966c-4442-97d0-4f4add815e9d",
    "sentence": "More generally, the sectors of the economy most adversely affected by the pandemic remain weak but have shown improvement.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210428.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20210428",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d0e39b53-87b7-4133-a6f1-64671d0eec15",
    "sentence": "Indeed, most central banks around the world aim to set inflation above zero, usually at about 2 percent.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20110427.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20110427",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d1d5fd5d-e8ab-42e9-8cb0-baddbe8371b4",
    "sentence": "As is always the case in setting policy, the FOMC will determine the timing and pace of policy normalization so as to promote its statutory mandate of maximum employment and price stability.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140917.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140917",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "91e816b5-ebde-400b-9a71-a742636102d8",
    "sentence": "Business fixed investment also appears to be growing at a slower pace than last year.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20190320",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6d55427a-ff28-436d-b690-a8fda2e1ca18",
    "sentence": "As emphasized in our statement, we will carefully monitor actual and expected inflation developments relative to our symmetric inflation goal.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20171213.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20171213",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "80398f87-b6a6-4aca-8b1a-5c71b4722c85",
    "sentence": "The labor force participation rate has moved up since late last year, particularly for individuals aged 25 to 54 years.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230920.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20230920",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5390d626-79a9-48eb-8bd5-a453492b919b",
    "sentence": "Notably, although the central tendency of the unemployment rate in late 2016 is slightly below its estimated longer-run value, and the central tendency for inflation is close to our 2 percent objective, the median projection for the federal funds rate at the end of 2016, at 2.9 percent, remains nearly a percentage point below the longer-run value of 3¾ percent or so projected by most participants.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20140917.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
    "date": "20140917",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "d2b02096-6ed8-47e0-8a89-dd29afeab071",
    "sentence": "The housing sector remains very strong, and business investment is increasing at a solid pace.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210728.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_prepared",
